value:
I owe the priestess a debt for saving
my little brothers. If she's in this
world, I'll help her however I can.

Right after I left to serve as a soldier,
the village was attacked by bandits.
Damn it, if only I'd stuck around...

Can't say I like fighting much. You're
the same way, right? I can see it in
your eyes.

The mountains here in Askr sure are
something else. They're so majestic,
I never get tired of looking at them.

I've used this axe to chop down
hundreds, if not thousands of trees.
All to keep my little brothers fed...

Name's Atlas. I'm a woodcutter.
I've got a little something for you
from $Nf.
Heck, I do this kinda thing to unwind!

Who's next?! I'm gonna beat the snot
outta you!

Guess my woodcutting skills aren't
as relevant as I thought...

Thanks! I'll pay you back for this on
the battlefield!

Name's Atlas. I'm just a woodcutter,
not some warrior, but if someone's in
trouble, I'll lend a hand!

I was just a woodcutter back home.
Never thought of myself as a hero
or anything grand like that.$k$pAnd it's not like I really understand
politics or religion. I always figured
that stuff was more for royals.$k$pBut I also ain't a lowlife who would
just turn a blind eye to someone in
trouble right in front of him.$k$pIf innocent lives are in danger, I'll
do whatever I can to help—even if
all I've got is this old axe.$k$pI can't just do nothing. Not after
everything I've seen.$k$pScorched villages, rivers of blood...
Not even the mountains themselves
are safe from the ravages of war.$k$pYou wanna put a stop to it too, don't
you? In that case, we've got our eyes
set on the same goal.$k$pOnce there's peace, I can go back
to being a simple woodcutter. So let's
get all this fighting over with!
I'll cut you down!
Don't you underestimate me!
You wanna brawl?!
Ready to fall? Bring it on!
Not here... Not...
Name's Atlas. I'm just a simple woodcutter.
Huh? The heck was that?! Oh... You call that a prank?
I ain't really cut out for being a warrior. I'm better suited for chopping trees, if you ask me.
Summoning? Divine Weapons? Sorry, friend, but you're gonna have to explain it simpler to me.
That priestess Celica has got smarts, sophistication, and on top of that, she's strong... She's just amazing.
Just you wait... Your big brother's definitely coming home...
I don't really like fighting, but if you need me to, I'll put my life on the line.
Can do.
Huh?
Timber!
